"Permanently Embedded Component" means inclusion of the Materials in a
manner intended to persist as part of a distributed product or
service, such that end users of that product or service receive the
benefit of the Materials without separately loading them. This
includes, without limitation: (a) use of the Materials as training
data or fine-tuning data for a model that is then distributed or made
available to third parties; (b) inclusion of the Materials in a system
prompt, prompt template, or instruction set that ships with, is
bundled into, or is fetched at runtime by a distributed product or
service; and (c) inclusion of the Materials in any binary, container
image, deployment artifact, or model weights distributed or operated
for third parties. Loading the Materials into an AI agent on a
per-session or per-project basis to assist with Your Own Work Product
is not a Permanently Embedded Component, even if that loading is
automated or repeated across sessions or projects.

"Competing Product" means any product or service whose principal value
proposition is to provide users with structured AI-readable
